

# Project Name

Enterprise Single Sign-On (SSO) Identity & Access Management System

---

# 1. Introduction

## 1.1 Purpose

یہ document ایک centralized SSO system کی requirements define کرتا ہے جس کے ذریعے multiple applications ایک ہی authentication اور authorization system استعمال کر سکیں گی۔

System کا مقصد:

* Single login experience provide کرنا
* User identity manage کرنا
* Roles اور permissions control کرنا
* Application level security provide کرنا
* Dynamic authorization implement کرنا

---

# 2. Project Scope

System following functionalities provide کرے گا:

## Authentication

* User Registration
* User Login
* Logout
* Password Reset
* Email Verification
* Token Based Authentication
* Refresh Token Management

## Authorization

* Role Based Access Control (RBAC)
* Permission Based Access Control
* User Specific Rights
* Dynamic Permission Mapping
* Attribute Based Authorization

## Application Management

* Multiple applications registration
* Client ID management
* Client Secret management
* Application wise access control

---

# 3. User Types

## 3.1 Super Admin

Responsibilities:

* Complete system control
* Create applications
* Manage users
* Create roles
* Assign permissions

---

## 3.2 Application Admin

Responsibilities:

* Manage application users
* Assign application rights
* View logs

---

## 3.3 Normal User

Responsibilities:

* Login
* Access allowed features
* Update profile

---

# 4. System Architecture

```
                Application 1
                     |
                Application 2
                     |
                Application 3

                     |
                     |

              SSO Identity Server

                     |

              Authentication DB

```

---

# 5. Functional Requirements

# Module 1: User Management

## User Registration

System shall allow:

* New user creation
* Email validation
* Password creation
* Profile information storage

Fields:

* Name
* Email
* Mobile
* Password
* Status

---

## Login

User shall login using:

* Email
* Password

System will:

1. Validate credentials
2. Check account status
3. Generate JWT token
4. Generate Refresh Token
5. Return access rights

---

# Module 2: Authentication

## JWT Token Generation

System shall generate:

Access Token

Contains:

```
UserId
Name
Roles
Permissions
Expiry
```

---

## Refresh Token

Features:

* Token rotation
* Expiry management
* Revocation

---

# Module 3: Role Management

Admin can:

* Create roles
* Update roles
* Delete roles

Examples:

```
Admin

Manager

Employee

Auditor

```

---

# Module 4: Permission Management

System shall support:

Function level permissions

Example:

```
USER.CREATE

USER.UPDATE

USER.DELETE

REPORT.VIEW

INVOICE.APPROVE

```

---

# Module 5: User Rights Mapping

Admin can assign:

User → Role

Example:

```
Ali

Role:
Manager

Permissions:

REPORT.VIEW
USER.UPDATE

```

---

# Module 6: Attribute Based Authorization

Developer can secure APIs/functions:

Example:

```
[Permission("USER.CREATE")]

CreateUser()

```

System automatically check کرے گا:

* Current user
* Assigned permissions
* Required permission

---

# Module 7: Application Management

Admin can register applications:

Example:

```
ERP System

CRM System

HR Portal

Mobile App

```

Application information:

```
Application Name

Client ID

Client Secret

Redirect URL

Status

```

---

# Module 8: NuGet Client Package

System provide کرے گا:

Package Name:

```
Company.SSO.Client

```

Install:

```
Install-Package Company.SSO.Client

```

Developer use:

```
services.AddSSO();

```

Package provide:

* JWT validation
* Permission checking
* Attribute authorization
* Middleware

---

# Module 9: Security Requirements

## Password Security

Password shall be stored using:

* PBKDF2
* BCrypt
* Argon2

Plain password storage prohibited.

---

# Token Security

Requirements:

* HTTPS mandatory
* Token expiry
* Refresh token rotation
* Token revocation

---

# API Security

Implement:

* JWT Authentication
* CORS policy
* Rate limiting
* Request validation

---

# 10. Database Requirements

## Users Table

```
Id

Name

Email

PasswordHash

Status

CreatedDate

```

---

## Roles Table

```
Id

RoleName

```

---

## Permissions Table

```
Id

Name

Code

```

---

## UserRoles

```
UserId

RoleId

```

---

## RolePermissions

```
RoleId

PermissionId

```

---

## RefreshTokens

```
UserId

Token

Expiry

Revoked

```

---

# 11. API Requirements

## Authentication APIs

POST

```
/api/auth/register

```

POST

```
/api/auth/login

```

POST

```
/api/auth/refresh-token

```

POST

```
/api/auth/logout

```

---

# User APIs

GET

```
/api/users

```

POST

```
/api/users/create

```

---

# Permission APIs

GET

```
/api/permissions

```

POST

```
/api/permissions/assign

```

---

# 12. Audit Logging

System maintain کرے گا:

* Login history
* Failed attempts
* Permission changes
* User activities

Fields:

```
UserId

Action

IP Address

DateTime

```

---

# 13. Non Functional Requirements

## Performance

System should support:

* Thousands of users
* Multiple applications
* High concurrent requests

---

## Availability

Target:

99.9% uptime

---

## Scalability

Support:

* Load balancing
* Multiple servers
* Cloud deployment

---

# 14. Deployment Requirements

Supported:

* Windows Server
* Linux
* Docker
* Kubernetes

Database:

* SQL Server
* PostgreSQL

---

# 15. Future Enhancements

Optional:

* Multi Factor Authentication
* OTP
* Google Authenticator
* Biometric Login
* Active Directory Integration
* Single Logout
* Mobile SDK

---

# 16. Acceptance Criteria

System approved when:

✔ User can register

✔ User can login

✔ JWT generated

✔ Roles assigned

✔ Permissions mapped

✔ Multiple applications authenticate

✔ NuGet package works

✔ Unauthorized users blocked

